00:15:13.007 --> 00:15:17.717
But this bizarre and nonsensical world would turn out to be one

00:15:17.887 --> 00:15:21.927
that was loved and enjoyed by children from all over the world, who

00:15:21.927 --> 00:15:25.537
had no idea about the original people the characters were based on.

00:15:26.717 --> 00:15:30.617
Caroll, of course, had no idea about how much of a resounding

00:15:30.687 --> 00:15:33.787
success it would be when he first started writing it.

00:15:34.707 --> 00:15:39.587
After writing the story, and unsure about what to do with it, Carroll spoke

00:15:39.587 --> 00:15:43.867
to his friend George Macdonald who was a successful author at the time.

00:15:45.057 --> 00:15:51.067
Macdonald took home the copy of Alice’s Adventures Underground to read it to his 6-year-old son.

00:15:52.317 --> 00:15:59.552
Unsurprisingly, and this seems to be a theme with children’s books, the boy absolutely loved it.

00:16:00.417 --> 00:16:06.457
